President Obama and his wife Michelle send their warmest wishes to Muslims celebrating Eid al-Adha. They recognize the holiday as a time to honor the sacrifice and commitment to God demonstrated by Abraham. It is also a celebration of how faith can unite people under the banners of fellowship and love. Muslims from all walks of life come together to pray, give alms, exchange gifts, and recommit to helping others. The President also mentions the millions of refugees around the world who are spending this holiday separated from their families, and he reaffirms the nation's commitment to welcoming strangers with empathy and an open heart. The President concludes by wishing a joyful Eid al-Adha to all those celebrating.